# FPGA Benchmarking for libnn

Record, compare, and analyze cycle-accurate performance data from FPGA board runs of libnn on AX45MPV.

## Quick Start (Recommended)

Use the scripts in `qemu-validate/`:

```bash
cd /home/nick/work/libnn/qemu-validate

# Step 1: Build the library (if not already built)
bash build_libnn.sh --verbose

# Step 2: Run a single function benchmark on FPGA
bash run_fpga_test.sh conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any --perf --tag baseline
```

### run_fpga_test.sh

Compiles a single unit test against `libnn.a` and runs it on the FPGA board via GDB/ICEman.

```bash
bash run_fpga_test.sh <test_name> [--port N] [--host H] [--perf] [--tag NAME]
```

| Option | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `--port N` | 1116 | FPGA board port |
| `--host H` | sw-boards.andestech.com | FPGA board host |
| `--perf` | off | Performance mode: ENA_MEASURE_PERF=1, large test case only |
| `--tag NAME` | (none) | Tag for log file naming (e.g. 'baseline', 'optimized') |

Key compilation flags applied automatically:
- `-mvh` — semihosting for GDB file I/O
- `-DGETENV_TESTDIR=...` — absolute path so binary finds `bin/*.bin` golden data
- `-DENA_RUN_TWICE` — runs function twice, measures warm-cache second run
- `-mext-vector=zve64d` — consistent with build_libnn.sh and run_qemu_test.sh

Output: log file saved to `qemu-validate/work/<test_name>_<tag>.log` with inst/cycle counts and pass/fail status.

### A/B Performance Comparison Workflow

```bash
cd /home/nick/work/libnn/qemu-validate

# 1. Build and benchmark baseline
bash build_libnn.sh --verbose
bash run_fpga_test.sh <func_name> --perf --tag baseline

# 2. Apply optimization, rebuild and benchmark
# ... edit source code ...
bash build_libnn.sh --verbose
bash run_fpga_test.sh <func_name> --perf --tag optimized

# 3. Compare results
cat work/<func_name>_baseline.log
cat work/<func_name>_optimized.log
```

## Full Suite Benchmark

For benchmarking all functions (takes several hours):

```bash
cd /home/nick/work/libnn/build_perf_ax45mpv
export PATH="/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH"
export MYPC=sw-boards.andestech.com
export MYPORT=1116
rm -f /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/First_Reset_done
../test.sh "" riscv64-elf-gcc \
  /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/riscv64-sim-wrapper-on-board \
  BOARD BS3 \
  "-mtune=andes-45-series -mext-vector -DNDS_VEC_RVV_VERSION=1000 \
   -DENA_RUN_TWICE -DENA_CACHEABLE_ENV_SETUP -lnn_v -mzfh \
   -DENA_TEST_PERF -DENA_DUMP_PARAMETERS"
```

### Data Location

Full-suite results are stored in `build_perf_ax45mpv/test_sh_<YYYYMMDDHHMMSS>/`:
```
performance.csv    # group, function, inst, cycle
parameter.csv      # group, function, test parameters
accuracy_fail_list # functions that failed accuracy check
log/               # per-function logs
adx/               # compiled test binaries
```

### Comparing Full-Suite Runs

```bash
# Full comparison table
python3 scripts/compare_perf.py old/performance.csv new/performance.csv

# Per-group summary
python3 scripts/compare_perf.py old/performance.csv new/performance.csv --summary

# Show only regressions > 5%
python3 scripts/compare_perf.py old/performance.csv new/performance.csv --regression --threshold 5

# Top 10 biggest improvements in convolution
python3 scripts/compare_perf.py old/performance.csv new/performance.csv --improvement --group convolution --top 10
```

